thiopia and Georgia. The fragments of Gelasius’ Ecclesiastical History are presented here systematically for the fi rst time. They are accompanied by the fragments of his doctrinal writings as well as all known testimonia about the bishop’s life and work. The edition is introduced by a thorough discussion of the sources and includes a facing English translation and notes.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh1 aMarinides, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarinides, Nicholas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStutz, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWallraff, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWallraff, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311047580740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047707840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110477078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110477078/original  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-076248-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017